70.1	Rosacea	Rosacea	Rosacea is a chronic condition characterized by facial erythema (redness). Pimples are sometimes included as part of the definition. Unless it affects the eyes, it is typically a harmless cosmetic condition. Treatment in the form of topical steroids can aggravate the condition.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Domenico_ghirlandaio%2C_ritratto_di_nonno_con_nipote.jpg/230px-Domenico_ghirlandaio%2C_ritratto_di_nonno_con_nipote.jpg
